metadata.content:
# Dwarf Star

Dwarf Star


Production information

Designer
Lax Torios


Cost
40,000 databits


[Source]


The Dwarf Star was a small-scale replica of the Galactic Empire's Death Star built by Lax Torios for planetary use on The Island of a planet. Prior to the Dwarf Star's creation, Lax Torios expressed that she wanted to build her own tiny Death Star, to which the other Castaways laughed at her. The laughing soon stopped, however, after she created it. She sold it at her vehicle shop for forty thousand databits. She also created two variants of her Dwarf Star, the blue, red, white, and yellow Beach Ball, and the green and red Bauble Battlestation.
metadata.title: Dwarf Star

# Vic Vankoh - Behind the scenes[]

Vic Vankoh's name was first revealed alongside the announcement of the animated special LEGO Star Wars Summer Vacation during the Summer of LEGO Star Wars panel at Star Wars Celebration Anaheim 2022. Vankoh later appeared in the trailer for the special, which released on June 21, 2022. The character was voiced by singer/comedian "Weird Al" Yankovic, who also performed a new song titled "Scarif Beach Party" for the film.
metadata.title: Vic Vankoh
